cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is about a learning framework for structured prediction tasks, which involves machine learning, natural language processing, and computer vision. The paper proposes a novel theoretical interpretation of the framework and performs experiments on various structured prediction tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
